    {
      "id": "2HSQManL9topVSg_75SyD",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 286.8828125,
      "y": 425.12890625,
      "width": 908.4594116210938,
      "height": 700,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a2",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2143659038,
      "version": 1175,
      "versionNonce": 1799828098,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1778276061812,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Functional requirements\n1. Users should be able to input a start location and a destination and get an estimate fare\n2. User should be able to request a ride based on an estimate\n3. Drivers should be able to accept/deny a request\n4. Drivers should be able to navigate to pickup/drop-off after navigating\n\n---- out of scope ---- \n- multiple car types\n- ratings for drivers and riders\n- schedule a ride in advance\n\n\n\nNon-functional requirements (Qualities, Constraints, Scale)\n- low latency matching < 1 min to match or failure\n- consistency of matching ride to driver is 1:1\n- highly available outside the matching\n- handle high throughput\n    - surges for peak hours\n    - surges for events\n\n----- out of scope ---- \nGDPR user privacy\nresilience and handling system failures\nmonitoring, logging, alerting\nCI/CD pipeline\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Functional requirements\n1. Users should be able to input a start location and a destination and get an estimate fare\n2. User should be able to request a ride based on an estimate\n3. Drivers should be able to accept/deny a request\n4. Drivers should be able to navigate to pickup/drop-off after navigating\n\n---- out of scope ---- \n- multiple car types\n- ratings for drivers and riders\n- schedule a ride in advance\n\n\n\nNon-functional requirements (Qualities, Constraints, Scale)\n- low latency matching < 1 min to match or failure\n- consistency of matching ride to driver is 1:1\n- highly available outside the matching\n- handle high throughput\n    - surges for peak hours\n    - surges for events\n\n----- out of scope ---- \nGDPR user privacy\nresilience and handling system failures\nmonitoring, logging, alerting\nCI/CD pipeline\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "OBkwWcZI-9crNjDB4KN5p",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1510.515625,
      "y": 421.77734375,
      "width": 345.77567274305574,
      "height": 817.0583737001386,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1192414494,
      "version": 764,
      "versionNonce": 1651104990,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1778275742553,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Core Entities\n- Ride\n- Driver\n- Rider\n- Location\n\n\nAPI\nPOST /ride/fare-estimate -> Partial<Ride>\n{\n    source, destination\n}\n\nPATCH /ride/request -> 200\n{\n    rideId\n} \n\nPOST /location/update\n{\n    lat, \n    long\n}\n\nPATCH /ride/driver/accept\n{\n    rideId,\n    rideAcceptanceStatus: bool\n}\n\nPATCH /ride/driver/update -> lat/long |\nnull\n{\n    rideId,\n    status: 'pickup' | 'droppedoff'\n}\n\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 16.341167474002773,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Core Entities\n- Ride\n- Driver\n- Rider\n- Location\n\n\nAPI\nPOST /ride/fare-estimate -> Partial<Ride>\n{\n    source, destination\n}\n\nPATCH /ride/request -> 200\n{\n    rideId\n} \n\nPOST /location/update\n{\n    lat, \n    long\n}\n\nPATCH /ride/driver/accept\n{\n    rideId,\n    rideAcceptanceStatus: bool\n}\n\nPATCH /ride/driver/update -> lat/long | null\n{\n    rideId,\n    status: 'pickup' | 'droppedoff'\n}\n\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
